                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/8241.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-06T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1913—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>333. Your August 5, 9 p.m. Governor Lind goes on a mission of peace and the
                    President feels sure his presence in Mexico will contribute toward a
                    satisfactory settlement of difficulties. The Mexican Government should await the
                    President’s communication and not give weight to misrepresentations of
                    sensational newspapers.</p>
                <p>You may make the foregoing statement to the Minister for Foreign Affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
